This function aggregates the abundance data at a specified taxonomic level. It accepts a phyloseq object or a data.frame as input.

T_collapse.Rd

This function aggregates the abundance data at a specified taxonomic level. It accepts a phyloseq object or a data.frame as input.

Usage

T_collapse (is_phyloseq=T, ps=..., names_level=...)

Arguments

ps

If "is_phyloseq = T", a phyloseq object, and "is_phyloseq = F" for data.frame.

T_table

(If is_phyloseq = F) A taxa table.

O_table

(If is_phyloseq = F) An OTUs/ASV table.

names_level

(If is_phyloseq = F) Taxonomic level to group (ex. class, genus).

Value

Returns a class array matrix at a selected taxonomic level.

Examples

# With BiocManager, package "microbiome"
library(microbiome)
#> Loading required package: phyloseq
